
[1]beforehand

   BEFO'REHAND, adv. [before and hand.] In a state of anticipation or
   preoccupation; often followed by with; as, you are before hand with me.

   1. Antecedently; by way of preparation or preliminary; aforetime.
   Math.13. 1 Tim.5.

   2. In a state of accumulation, so as that more has been received than
   expended. A man is beforehand. In this use it is more properly an
   adjective.

   3. At first; before any thing is done.
